com.n9mtq4.logwindow

Class BaseConsole

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.n9mtq4.logwindow.BaseConsole

  • public class BaseConsole
extends java.lang.Object
    The class that handles all User to Listener interactions.

    This class is an internal server with multiple different components.
    There are the ListenerAttributes. These receive events from the BaseConsole. AdditionEvent, EnableEvent, ObjectEvent, DisableEvent, RemovalEvent, and anything implementing GenericEvent. The BaseConsole handles the AdditionEvent, EnableEvent, DisableEvent, and the RemovalEvent. To push an event call push(Object) or pushNow(Object).
    There are also ConsoleUIs. These receive output from the BaseConsole. The ConsoleUIs are responsible for displaying the output, or sending it via packets, etc.

    Created by Will on 10/20/14.

    Since:
    v0.1
    See Also:
    ListenerAttribute, ConsoleUI
